# 02_Attack_Simulations
**Project:** Attack simulation against Windows endpoint to generate SIEM events  
**Objective:** Simulate common attack techniques (brute-force, port scanning, file drop) from Kali Linux and confirm detections in Wazuh.

---

## Attack types covered
- SSH / RDP Brute Force (T1110)
- Port Scan (T1046)
- Suspicious Process Launch (PowerShell abuse, T1059)
- EICAR / benign malware test (detection by AV & EDR)

---

## Setup (pre-requisite)
- Wazuh Server running and reachable
- Wazuh Agent installed on Windows 10 VM
- Kali Linux VM on same NAT/host-only network

Example IPs:
- Wazuh: `192.168.56.10`
- Windows: `192.168.56.20`
- Kali: `192.168.56.30`

---

